The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Thursday, September 12, 2002 				 Lawyers protest
 OUR LEGAL REPORTER																								Calcutta, Sept. 11: Lawyers across the state will stay away from courts on September 18 to protest against the amendment of the Civil Procedure Code (CPC) and Legal Services Authorities Act by the Centre, chairman of West Bengal Bar Council Amiya Kumar Chatterjee said today.																								He said in a meeting on September 7 the All India Bar Council decided that it would ask its members across the country not to attend the courts on September 18 to protest against the anti-people amendment of CPC.
